text.section:
"Do construction business" means to agree to:
pave or curb a sidewalk, street, or other public or private property;
excavate earth, rock, or other material for a foundation or other purpose; or
do work on or in a building or other structure that requires the use of a building material, including:
paint;
stone;
brick;
mortar;
wood;
cement;
structural iron;
structural steel;
sheet iron;
galvanized iron;
metallic piping;
tin;
lead;
electric wiring; or
any other metal.
